    "history" -> {"12", "14.0", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"Majorana fermion", "Dirac fermion"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "ToDirac[expr, {h1, ..., hn, h n + 1, ..., h 2 n} -> {c1, c2, ..., cn}] \
converts expr written in Majorana fermion modes {h1, h2, ..., h 2 n} into an \
equivalent form in terms of the Dirac fermion modes {c1, c2, ..., cn} via a \
suitable transformation between them. ToDirac[expr, {h1, h n + 1} -> c1, ..., \
{h n, h 2 n} -> c n] is the same. ToDirac[{h1, ..., hn, h n + 1, ..., h 2 n} \
-> {c1, c2, ..., cn}] or ToDirac[{h1, h n + 1} -> c1, ..., {h n, h 2 n} -> c \
n] returns a list of replacement rules to be applied later. ToDirac[vec] \
converts the coefficients vector vec in a linear combination of Majorana \
fermion operators into coefficients of Dirac fermion annihilation and \
creation operators. ToDirac[mat] converts the coefficients matrix mat in a \
bilinear combination of Majorana fermion operators into coefficients of Dirac \
fermion annihilation and creation operators.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "ToDirac", "titlemodifier" -> "", 
    "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "ToDirac", "type" -> "Symbol", 
    "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/ToDirac"}},
